// Changelog:
// 2.4.5 - Proportional speed floor: replaced fixed 50 mph cutoff with
//         max(10, trackLength × 10) so short tracks like Sewage (1.5mi → 15 mph floor)
//         record properly while long tracks still filter early-race noise.
//         Migration floor lowered to absolute minimum of 10 mph to match.
// 2.4.4 - Critical fix: raceData.imagePath is the track SVG outline, NOT a car image URL.
//         Revert car resolution to DOM-only (parseCarImg/currentCar). Add migration step
//         to purge corrupted SVG strings from data.car in existing storage.
//         Date column widened to 24% in lobby colgroup.
// 2.4.3 - Fix Best Laps columns cut off in lobby panel: reduce flex min-width from
//         300px to 220px, add table-layout:fixed + colgroup proportional widths,
//         overflow:hidden + text-overflow:ellipsis on td to prevent blowout.
// 2.4.2 - CSS fix: add overflow-x:auto to .rslogPanel and min-width to tables so
//         the Best Lap (and Speed) tables scroll horizontally instead of overflowing
//         outside the widget container.
// 2.4.1 - Confirmed raceData field names from live payload: track = raceData.title,
//         car = raceData.imagePath + imageID + '/small.png'. Removed dev logger.
// 2.4.0 - Add CAR_CLASSES map (sourced from Torn wiki) with coloured class badges
//         (A=gold, B=silver, C=blue, D=green, E=grey) in all four tables and both CSV exports.
// 2.3.0 - Store top speed as raw float (full precision) instead of rounding to 2dp before storage.
//         CSV export now writes the full value. Display stays at toFixed(2).
// 2.2.0 - Bug fixes:
//         [1] Speed floor raised from >0 to >10 mph to filter near-zero lap-wrap spikes
//         [2] updateTopSpeed: ignore speeds below 50 mph (implausible top-speed samples)
//         [3] migrateSpeedLog: zero out existing topSpeed entries below 50 mph on first run
//         [4] parseBestLapFromResponse: read track/car from raceData payload first,
//             fall back to DOM — prevents stale globals mis-attributing laps during
//             lobby transition (was causing duplicate 43.3s entries across different combos)
//         [5] Added raceData key logger (console.log, dev aid, remove after confirming field names)

